The Transport Department is being called upon to investigate why more than 20 trucks were attacked on Thursday night. For more on this, Anlie Hattingh spoke to Patrick O’Leary from FleetWatch truck magazine. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng police are expected to deploy additional resources in Heidelberg. This in response to the torching of trucks on the N3 between Heidelberg and Vosloorus. READ: Suspect arrested for torching trucks on N3 It is alleged the trucks were petrol bombed by occupants of several vehicles. The motive behind the arson attacks is still unknown.